as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+5+9]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + animals_matter_a_lot + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJzFWG1z00gS%2FitdFNTZ2ciWnGTZhMqHvDhAEdhckl32jlBmLI2tWUsaMTOKYlj2t98zI8lvsUO4%2B3BUURhppvvp7qff9PVJxEesSMyJjPiTgyfdLh0eHtK1YiIjIylU7MsUP8qMboqeH%2BxSKVUS3QpeUhkMeoOdwe5gb7BPLW1kTvtte%2F0mg5gjrYs0N0JmFMaQdkA%2B5UzJMBYsscKC%2FR4FNGJqwEo2HcRFyjLdvOgRy0TKEj3QMuVlzEzzZodGhSkUry8MUmYMV4NSmHgQCR3KIjMiGzfHdymTi88HS7ebU3szdbU4NkjkTOU%2BJeLW3hXZQIu0SJg1y1nZZ2FMbG6q0MToYmpi%2FB6JhBPcOH%2Btu2SsKSyK9DYpDt%2BLjGuSyglT3IOHWMqBQGg8NzGvnPcPDauz0Ml4QaFMc6mtkbMDuJtFHBLxSGgnTRuWRSyRGacUwU069GkWu%2F7tJwvVXud3OQ8NLt6ypOAkR07CPMwdJ%2ByYa0PDYkqFVWMvar5o2AFdxUqkOb3nCULK6ULJPyG3uv2y%2F65%2FeXTdP6XhlMY844oZ3smnDad4JMySm7bwchuRMxUY60lIcrJ%2By0KujDU5lQpMmnlMV2crd7A8TwTXHbqapp1EjjOpEN7W13xvm%2FL9vW9tJ8tFa99%2FRievX7iTQ25Y9TRXcsiGIhEGQIbSmh3ZhPjgb1PwsUNnLDQSOmFrJQoHchuDzGyTlsQtMaQaI3L9D%2BXp0fm%2Fuk8%2F0pAnsgTn7V0XYX6H38kU1yEbXnWyoDsqQlPFAtHjYCrMr5h7WnOZDpE9ZE%2FjoWdEyuknCplh2iiZ45olclY4qpJlI1NeJaGOdOuSpZpPu1fwXUZ%2F%2B8%2B6U0W3mt5JFcWs0PR30NmzD19A0SGCQU0awXnzNDiRNq8K2HI4c2Er2LalwKK7aM2PkiqQcmDkmHgmi3FMI%2Bm4ZMHVad1uOHEsrSEp9Xx%2Fpw79q