D" id="w1_2_3_4_6"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f2ccc0;strokeColor=#c96a4a;fontColor=#5a2410;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1239" y="478" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Living in&lt;br&gt;a simulation&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+4+6+9]&lt;br&gt;→ AI safety (Redwood Research)&lt;br&gt;(Nick Bostrom)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + no_discounting_future_humans + suffering_focused + living_in_simulation&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If most observers like us are simulated, the astronomical future that justified x-risk work probably gets switched off long before it happens. The same expected-value reasoning that bought astronomical stakes now attenuates them: future-facing value is multiplied by the probability the simulation keeps running, and the ranking slides back toward the present. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 4 no_discounting_future_humans → 6 suffering_focused → 9 living_in_simulation" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJzFWWtz2zYW%2FSt3Mums5JoSKdtJ7Iw%2F%2BCEnmbita7tNd%2BOMApGQiIokGAA0raTpb98DkNTDkhxnZzqbmUwYELj33PcB9eVJxEesSMyJjPiTgyfdLh0eHtK1YiIjIylU7PMUD2VGN0XPD3aplCqJbgUvqQwGvcHOYHfwbLBPLW1kTvtte%2Fwmg5gjrYs0N0JmFMaQdkA%2B5UzJMBYsscKC%2FR4FNGJqwEo2HcRFyjLdvOgRy0TKEj3QMuVlzEzzZodGhSkUrw8MUmYMV4NSmHgQCR3KIjMiGzfbdymTi%2BuDpdPNrmeki9GIK7dBhoXmUfNqnxJxa9dFNtAiLRJmbXIm9lkYE5vbKTQxupiaGM8jkXCCD%2BevdZeMtYNFkd4mxeF4kXFNUjlhintwD0s5rBEa6ybmlef%2BpWFyFjoZLymUaS61tXC2AWeziEMiloR20rRhWcQSmXFKEdmkQx9ngevffrRQ7XF%2Bl%2FPQ4OAtSwpOcuQkzGPcccKOuTY0LKZUWDX2oOaLhh3Q0RvSbMTNlFqXPCqljOgSm5gK43Yl41X%2F5%2F7l0XX%2FlIZTGvOMK2Z4J582acUjYZactYWX2wieqSBZf0KSk%2FVbFnJlrOGpVEimmd90tbdyCsvzRHDdoatp2knkOJMKCdX6ku9tU76%2F97XtZLmY7fs%2F0Mmbl27nkBtWreZKDtlQJMIAyFBa4yNbE%2B%2F9bQo%2BdOiMhUZCJ1O8EoUNuY1EZrZJS%2BI2PaQaI3799%2BXp0fm%2Fu08%2F0J